ENTRY            D4285   20260413   20260528   20260528       D152
SUBENT        D4285001   20260413   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                 14         52
TITLE      Deuteron induced reactions on Ho and La: Experimental
            excitation functions and comparison with code results
AUTHOR     (A.Hermanne, R.Adam-Rebeles, F.Tarkanyi, S.Takacs,
           J.Csikai, M.P.Takacs, A.Ignatyuk)
INSTITUTE  (3HUNDEB,2BLGVUB,3HUNKOS,4RUSFEI)
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/B,311,102,2013)
           #doi:10.1016/j.nimb.2013.06.014
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2BLGLVN)
           (ISOCY,2JPNTOH)
SAMPLE     (57-LA-139,NAT=0.9991)
           (57-LA-138,NAT=0.0009)
           (67-HO-165,NAT=1.0)
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
METHOD     (ACTIV,EXTB,EDEG,GSPEC,MOSEP,STTA) Irradiations of
            165Ho targets were carried out using stacked foil
            technique and high-resolution gamma spectrometry at
            LLN (50 MeV) and Tohoku University (40 MeV).
           At 50 MeV, 22 Ho foils (29.2 um) with Sm foils were
            interleaved with Al monitor/degrader foils and
            irradiated at 120 nA (+/-5%) for 3960 sec. At 40 MeV,
            10 Ho foils with Rh, Au, Yb, MnCuNi alloy, and MoRe
            alloy foils were irradiated with Al monitor/degrader
            foils for 1800 sec at 64 nA under He gas cooling.
           Irradiations of 139La targets were performed at LLN
            with a 50 MeV deuteron beam using 23 La foils (97 um)
            with Tl/Cu targets and Al monitor/degrader foils for
            2310 sec at 115 nA.
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(D,X)11-NA-22,,SIG)
           (13-AL-27(D,X)11-NA-24,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (,F.TARKANYI+,R,IAEA-NDS-1211,2001)
ERR-ANALYS (EN-ERR) The uncertainty in median foil energy arises
            from beam energy uncertainty, foil thickness
            variations affecting stopping power, and energy
            straggling effects.
           (ERR-T) Total uncertainty is due to:
           (ERR-1) Surface density of target nuclei (5%)
           (ERR-2) Incident charged particle flux (5%)
           (ERR-3) Nuclear decay and branching data (5%)
           (ERR-4,3.,5.) Detector efficiency (3-5%)
           (ERR-S,1.0,8.0) Statistical and peak fitting (1-8%)
           This approach results in an overall uncertainty
            of 12-15% for the radionuclides studied.
ADD-RES    (THEO) The experimental data were compared to the
           results of the theoretical model codes TENDL-2012,
           ALICE-D and EMPIRE-D.
           (COMP) The measured experimental data were compared to
           those found in the literature.
           (TTY-C) Fitted excitation functions were used for
           determination of integral physical yields.
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry was checked by the corresponding author.
HISTORY    (20130819C)
           (20260413A) VT. Entry revised
ENDBIB              52
COMMON               3          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
5.         5.         5.
ENDCOMMON            3
